.SH "NAME"
pci_disable_device \- Disable PCI device after use
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ pci_disable_device('u
.BI "void pci_disable_device(struct\ pci_dev\ *\ " "dev" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
PCI device to be disabled
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Signal to the system that the PCI device is not in use by the system anymore\&. This only involves disabling PCI bus\-mastering, if active\&.
.PP
Note we don\*(Aqt actually disable the device until all callers of
\fBpci_enable_device\fR
have called
\fBpci_disable_device\fR\&.
